    public class Rotation2d
extends java.lang.Object

    Taken from Team 254 2017 Code. A rotation in a 2d coordinate frame represented a point on the unit circle (cosine and sine). Inspired by Sophus (https://github.com/strasdat/Sophus/tree/master/sophus)

      • normalize

        public void normalize()
        From trig, we know that sin^2 + cos^2 == 1, but as we do math on this object we might accumulate rounding errors. Normalizing forces us to re-scale the sin and cos to reset rounding errors.

      • interpolate

        public Rotation2d interpolate(Rotation2d other,
                              double x)
        Description copied from interface: Interpolable
        Interpolates between this value and an other value according to a given parameter. If x is 0, the method should return this value. If x is 1, the method should return the other value. If 0 < x < 1, the return value should be interpolated proportionally between the two.
        Specified by:
        interpolate in interface Interpolable<Rotation2d>
        Parameters:
        other - The value of the upper bound
        x - The requested value. Should be between 0 and 1.
        Returns:
        Interpolable The estimated average between the surrounding data
